ECrew%20members%20then%20insisted%20that%20Hernandez-Garnier%20deboard%20the%20plane.%20He%20and%20his%20female%20companion%2C%20Yusleydis%20Blanca%20Loyola%2C%2032%2C%20refused%20to%20disembark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20American%20Airlines%20told%20Business%20Insider%3A%20%26quot%3BDuring%20boarding%20of%20American%20Airlines%20flight%201858%20on%20Aug.%2019%20with%20service%20from%20Miami%20(MIA)%20to%20Las%20Vegas%20(LAS)%2C%20two%20customers%20became%20disruptive%20and%20were%20non-compliant%20with%20crew%20member%20instructions.%20Law%20enforcement%20responded%20and%20removed%20both%20customers%20from%20the%20aircraft.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20arrest%20report%2C%20Loyola%20told%20crew%20members%20%26quot%3Bthat%20if%20they%20could%20not%20fly%2C%20no%20one%20else%20can%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolice%20were%20called%20to%20the%20plane%20and%20warned%20the%20pair%20that%20they%20would%20be%20arrested%20if%20they%20did%20not%20comply.%20Both%20once%20again%20refused.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlanca%20Loyola%20started%20live-streaming%20the%20incident%20on%20TikTok%20and%20was%20seen%20explaining%20that%20Hernandez-Garnier%20had%20just%20had%20surgery.%20A%20mugshot%20of%20Hernandez-Garnier%20published%20by%20Miami-Dade%20police%20shows%20his%20bloodied%20head%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fman-bleeding-after-hair-transplant-arrested-for-refusing-to-leave-plane-at-miami-airport-13200529%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESky%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20the%20result%20of%20a%20hair%20transplant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20each%20face%20two%20charges%20of%20trespassing%20and%20resisting%20arrest%20without%20violence%2C%20according%20to%20records%20published%20online%20by%20the%20Miami-Dade%20County%20Clerk%20of%20Courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20the%20American%20Airlines%20flight%20was%20significantly%20delayed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3