20to%20perform%20stand-up%20comedy%20in%20person%20is%20in%20itself%20a%20rebellious%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20the%20only%20Indian%20stand-up%20comedian%20with%20spina%20bifida%20has%20made%20Sweta%20aware%20that%20her%20comedy%20has%20a%20deeper%20purpose%3A%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20issues%20confronting%20people%20with%20disabilities%20and%20to%20ask%20her%20audience%20to%20think%20more%20deeply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mandar%20Latkar%2C%20a%20peer%20in%20the%20stand-up%20comedy%20scene%20who%20has%20witnessed%20her%20craft%20up%20close%2C%20Sweta%20excels%20at%20addressing%20tough%20issues%20with%20humour.%20%E2%80%9CSweta%20boldly%20addresses%20challenging%20themes%2C%20including%20her%20personal%20experiences%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20afraid%20to%20confront%20topics%20that%20might%20have%20once%20been%20uncomfortable%20for%20her.%20He%20also%20highlights%20that%20Sweta%20wraps%20up%20her%20comedy%20sets%20with%20a%20segment%20focused%20on%20educating%20the%20audience%20about%20disability%20and%20correcting%20common%20misconceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20she%20believes%20her%20voice%20has%20changed%20over%20the%20years%20to%20better%20connect%20with%20her%20audiences%2C%20she%20responds%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20my%20voice%20has%20changed%20dramatically.%E2%80%9D%20Sweta%20remains%20committed%20to%20her%20voice%20but%20has%20refined%20how%20she%20discusses%20her%20experiences.%20%E2%80%9CChoosing%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20certain%20things%20has%20never%20been%20an%20option%20for%20me%2C%20and%20it%20never%20will%20be%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20states%20firmly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20writing%20comedy%2C%20Sweta%20finds%20meaning%20in%20her%20advocacy%20work%20for%20individuals%20with%20disabilities.%20Why%20does%20she%20do%20it%3F%20%E2%80%9CBecause%20disability%20isn%E2%80%99t%20the%20problem%2C%20accessibility%2C%20or%